      problemStatement: 'Atolls gets 50+ Glassdoor reviews per week. HR-Lead Karla spent 2–3 hours daily on them — and trends were getting lost.',
      problemContext: 'Read, tag, reply in Atolls voice, post to Glassdoor — manually, one review at a time. The worst part: a review about "toxic management culture" got answered as a single item, instead of being flagged as a warning sign. Karla was stuck between reaction and strategy. The real problem wasn\'t technical — it was cultural. How could a system support HR without fully automating? How could an AI reproduce Atolls\' tone if even the HR team couldn\'t formalise it?',
