      /* ── Learnings ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      learnings: [
        "Tone first, tech second. If AI is meant to feel human, document the human BEFORE writing code. A style guide is worth more than three days of prompt iteration.",
        "Constraints are features. Karla didn't want full automation — she wanted 10-second approves. \"Boring\" Approve/Edit buttons built more trust than \"cool\" magic.",
        'Real client = exponential learning. Karla\'s 40 Excel reviews were more valuable than any hypothesis. Pattern analysis showed "salary" was a top-3 keyword — we never would have guessed.',
        'Workarounds are solutions. No Glassdoor API, no company guidelines, no complete data — workarounds became the design principle, and the solution was better for being real.',
